{"CHIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to Chios, an island in the Ægean Sea.","pos":""}],"CHIAROSCURIST":[{"def":"A painter who cares for and studies light and shade rather than color.","pos":""},{"def":"A commissure; especially, the optic commissure, or crucial union of the optic nerves.","pos":""}],"CHIASMUS":[{"def":"An inversion of the order of words or phrases, when repeated or subsequently referred to in a sentence; thus, If e'er to bless thy sons My voice or hands deny, These hands let useful skill forsake, This voice in silence die.","pos":""}],"CHIASTOLITE":[{"def":"A variety of andalusite; -- called also macle.","pos":""}]}